name: Nadal
summary: Rafael Nadal has recently competed in the Madrid Open after recovering from an injury, defeating Alex de Minaur in the second round, much to the delight of the home crowd. Despite the victory, Nadal has expressed uncertainty about his participation in the upcoming French Open, stating that he would not play if he is unable to compete effectively. This has led to speculation about his potential retirement, with some suggesting that the Madrid Open may have been his farewell tournament. However, Nadal has welcomed additional support in Madrid this year, indicating that he is still actively engaged in the sport. Additionally, Novak Djokovic has expressed his desire to play Nadal at least one more time before he retires.
